# Nuxt UI + Tailwind Colors Cheat Sheet

## Theming with Tailwind

```css
@import "tailwindcss";
@import "@nuxt/ui";

@theme {
  /* Custom theme tokens */
  --font-sans: 'Public Sans', system-ui, sans-serif;
  --font-mono: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
}
```

## Colors: Semantic Map

| Semantic    | Default | Use                                   |
|-------------|---------|---------------------------------------|
| primary     | green   | Main CTAs, active UI, brand           |
| secondary   | blue    | Secondary actions, alt UI             |
| success     | green   | Success, confirmations                |
| info        | blue    | Info, neutral alerts                  |
| warning     | yellow  | Warnings, attention-needed            |
| error       | red     | Errors, destructive actions           |
| neutral     | slate   | Background, text, borders, disabled   |

**Usage:**  
```vue
<UButton color="success">Save</UButton>
```

**Add or Override Colors (main.css):**
```css
@theme static {
  /* Custom/override shades */
  --color-brand-500: #ef4444;
  --color-green-400: #00DC82;
  /* ... all shades 50-950 ... */
}
```

## Runtime Color Mapping

`app.config.ts` (for dynamic assignment of semantic colors):
```ts
export default defineAppConfig({
  ui: {
    colors: {
      primary: 'brand',   // or any color you've defined in @theme
      secondary: 'blue',
      neutral: 'zinc'
    }
  }
})
```

> Only use color names that match Tailwind or those you define in `@theme`.


